  "title": "event manager",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Overview:</strong> We are seeking Event Manager to execute and ensuring overall outlet success.</h3><h2><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></h2><h2>teamwork, giving customers a happy and joyous experience and good coordination.</h2><h3><strong>Planning and Organization</strong></h3><ol><li>Developing event concepts, themes, and objectives based on client requirements.</li><li>Creating detailed project timelines and budgets.</li><li>Identifying and booking venues suitable for the event type and audience.</li></ol><h3><strong>Coordination and Logistics</strong></h3><ol><li>Coordinating with vendors, suppliers, caterers, decorators, and entertainers.</li><li>Managing permits, licenses, and compliance with local regulations.</li><li>Overseeing event setup, breakdown, and on-site logistics.</li></ol><h3><strong>Client and Stakeholder Communication</strong></h3><ol><li>Acting as the primary point of contact for clients, stakeholders, and team members.</li><li>Ensuring client needs are met while staying within budget and on schedule.</li></ol><h3><strong>Team Management</strong></h3><ol><li>Delegating tasks to staff and ensuring proper execution.</li><li>Supervising event-day operations, including troubleshooting and problem-solving.</li></ol><h3><strong>Marketing and Promotion</strong></h3><ol><li>Developing promotional strategies and materials for public-facing events.</li><li>Managing event sales, registrations, or RSVP processes.</li></ol><h3><strong>Budget and Financial Oversight</strong></h3><ol><li>Tracking expenses and reconciling budgets post-event.</li><li>Negotiating contracts to secure cost-effective deals.</li></ol><h3><strong>Risk Management</strong></h3><ol><li>Preparing contingency plans for emergencies or unforeseen issues.</li><li>Ensuring safety protocols are in place and communicated to all participants.</li></ol><h3><strong>Evaluation and Reporting</strong></h3><ol><li>Collecting feedback from attendees, vendors, and clients.</li><li>Analyzing the success of the event and preparing detailed post-event reports.</li></ol><h3><strong>Creative Problem-Solving</strong></h3><ol><li>Addressing last-minute changes or issues with flexibility and efficiency.</li><li>Enhancing the attendee experience with innovative ideas and attention to detail.</li></ol><p>Job Type: Full-time</p>",
